What is Pullulan?
Pullulan is an extracellular, water-soluble polysaccharide produced through the fermentation of a black yeast called Aureobasidium pullulans, discovered by R. Bauer in 1938. This unique polymer is non-toxic, edible, and possesses excellent film-forming, adhesive, and oxygen barrier properties. Its versatility makes it suitable for a wide range of applications across food, pharmaceutical, and cosmetic industries, serving as an effective alternative to synthetic polymers.
